trans-unit.source: Before you run the application, you must ensure that you have created a <token>servicensd</token> and obtained a SAS key, as described in <link xlink:href="c86a81be-caa5-4246-ac8c-82a70819a28b" xmlns:xlink="http://www.w3.org/1999/xlink">Step 1: Introduction and Prerequsites</link>.

trans-unit.source: Open an Internet browser and visit the <externalLink><linkText>Azure Management Portal</linkText><linkUri>http://manage.windowsazure.com</linkUri></externalLink>.
trans-unit.target: Open an Internet browser and visit the <externalLink><linkText>Azure Management Portal</linkText><linkUri>http://manage.windowsazure.com</linkUri></externalLink>.

trans-unit.source: Click <ui>Service Bus</ui> in the left-hand tree.
trans-unit.target: Click <ui>Service Bus</ui> in the left-hand tree.

trans-unit.source: Click the name of the <token>servicensd</token> that you want to use.
trans-unit.target: Click the name of the <token>servicensd</token> that you want to use.

trans-unit.source: At the bottom of the page, click <ui>Connection Information</ui>.
trans-unit.target: At the bottom of the page, click <ui>Connection Information</ui>.

trans-unit.source: Make a note of the connection string with SAS key, or copy it to the clipboard.
trans-unit.target: Make a note of the connection string with SAS key, or copy it to the clipboard.

trans-unit.source: In <token>vs_current_short</token>, from the <ui>Debug</ui> menu, click <ui>Start Debugging</ui>, or press <ui>F5</ui>.
trans-unit.target: In <token>vs_current_short</token>, from the <ui>Debug</ui> menu, click <ui>Start Debugging</ui>, or press <ui>F5</ui>.
